$ /dev/dxg

`/dev/dxg` exposes a set of IOCTL that closely mimic the native WDDM D3DKMT kernel service layer on Windows. This makes it possible to expose
→ hardware/xPU/GPU[GPUs] under the control of a Windows host to → Linux/kernel/process[processes] running in → Windows/Subsystem-for-Linux.

sa:

  → Windows/Subsystem-for-Linux#wsl-gpu[Using GPUs in WSL]

  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/drivers/dxgkrnl_sys[`C:\Windows\System32\drivers\dxgkrnl.sys`]

 `→ Linux/kernel/source/drivers/hv/dxgkrnl`

links:
  → https://github.com/microsoft/libdxg

  → https://github.com/microsoft/WSL2-Linux-Kernel/tree/linux-msft-wsl-6.1.y/drivers/hv/dxgkrnl

  → https://devblogs.microsoft.com/directx/directx-heart-linux/[DirectX is coming to the Windows Subsystem for Linux]
